@startuml approach1-sql-detailed-activity
title **Approach 1: InMemoryContainer — SQL Query Flow (Detailed)**

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #666

|Test Code|
start
:Call **InMemoryContainer.GetItemQueryIterator<T>**
(queryText, continuationToken, requestOptions);

|InMemoryContainer|
:Call **FilterItemsByQuery**
(queryText, parameters, requestOptions);

|CosmosSqlParser|
:**Parse**(queryText);
:Build **CosmosSqlQuery** AST record:
• SelectFields
• Where (expression tree)
• OrderBy (fields + directions)
• GroupBy
• Distinct, Top, Offset, Limit;

|InMemoryContainer.FilterItemsByQuery|
:**GetAllItemsForPartition**(requestOptions)
→ List<string> from ConcurrentDictionary
→ filter by partition key if specified
→ exclude TTL-expired items;

:**AugmentWithComputedProperties**()
→ add virtual properties for
computed property definitions;

:**ExpandFromSource**()
→ handle FROM c IN c.arrayField
→ iterate array elements as rows;

:**ExpandAllJoins**()
→ flatten JOINed arrays
→ cross-product with parent document;

#LightYellow:=== WHERE clause evaluation ===
**EvaluateWhereExpression**(expr, JObject item)
per item in collection|

|InMemoryContainer.EvaluateSqlExpression|
:Recursively evaluate SQL expression:;

note right
  **LiteralExpression** → return constant
  **IdentifierExpression** → lookup property in JObject
  **PropertyAccessExpression** → navigate nested paths (c.address.city)
  **IndexAccessExpression** → array indexing (c.tags[0])
  **BinaryExpression** → =, !=, <, >, <=, >=, +, -, *, /, %, ||, AND, OR
  **UnaryExpression** → NOT, Negate, BitwiseNot
  **FunctionCallExpression** → 40+ built-in functions:
    UPPER, LOWER, CONTAINS, STARTSWITH, ENDSWITH,
    ARRAY_CONTAINS, ARRAY_LENGTH, ARRAY_SLICE,
    ST_DISTANCE, ST_WITHIN, ST_INTERSECTS,
    CONCAT, SUBSTRING, REPLACE, TRIM, LENGTH,
    ABS, FLOOR, CEILING, ROUND, POWER, SQRT, LOG,
    ToString, IS_DEFINED, IS_NULL, IS_NUMBER, etc.
  **BetweenExpression** → BETWEEN low AND high
  **InExpression** → IN (val, val, …)
  **LikeExpression** → LIKE pattern [ESCAPE char]
  **TernaryExpression** → condition ? ifTrue : ifFalse
  **CoalesceExpression** → left ?? right
  **SubqueryExpression** → (SELECT …) — recursive
  **ArrayLiteralExpression** → [expr, expr, …]
  **ObjectLiteralExpression** → {key: expr, key: expr}
end note

:Return bool (include/exclude item);

|InMemoryContainer.FilterItemsByQuery|

:**ApplyGroupBy**() + aggregate functions
→ COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX
→ group items by GROUP BY fields
→ apply HAVING clause if present;

:**ApplyOrderByFields**()
→ multi-field sort
→ ASC / DESC per field
→ uses EvaluateSqlExpression for sort keys;

:Apply **TOP** → Take(TopCount);

:Apply **OFFSET + LIMIT**
→ Skip(Offset).Take(Limit);

:**ProjectFields**()
→ SELECT projection
→ named fields, aliased expressions
→ nested objects, computed expressions
→ SELECT * returns all fields;

:**StripComputedProperties**()
→ remove virtual properties from
SELECT * projections;

:Apply **DISTINCT**
→ deduplicate on projected shape
→ JSON string comparison;

:**UnwrapValueSelect**()
→ SELECT VALUE → extract scalar
from wrapper object;

:Return List<string> (JSON documents);

|InMemoryContainer|
:Deserialize each JSON string →
**JsonConvert.DeserializeObject<T>()**;

:Create **new InMemoryFeedIterator<T>**
(items, maxItemCount, initialOffset);

:Return **FeedIterator<T>** to caller;

|Test Code|
while (FeedIter.HasMoreResults?) is (yes)
  :Call **ReadNextAsync()**;

  |InMemoryFeedIterator<T>|
  :**EnsureItems**()
  → lazily evaluate factory delegate
  if provided (deferred execution);

  :Paginate: **Skip**(offset).**Take**(maxItemCount)
  → extract current page of items;

  :Generate **continuation token**
  → offset-based integer
  → null if this is the last page;

  :Create **new InMemoryFeedResponse<T>**
  (page of items, continuationToken,
  Headers: x-ms-request-charge,
  x-ms-activity-id);

  |Test Code|
  :Receive **FeedResponse<T>**
  → .Resource (items)
  → .ContinuationToken
  → .RequestCharge
  → .Count;

endwhile (no)

stop

@enduml
